=begin pod
=head2 set-lower

Sets the minimum value of the adjustment.

When setting multiple adjustment properties via their individual
setters, multiple I<changed> signals will
be emitted. However, since the emission of the
I<changed> signal is tied to the emission
of the I<notify> signals of the changed properties, itâ€™s possible
to compress the I<changed> signals into one
by calling L<.freeze-notify() and .thaw-notify() found in Gnome::GObject::Object|/content-docs/api2/reference/GObject/Object#freeze-notify> around the calls to the individual setters.

Alternatively, using a single L<.object-set() in Gnome::GObject::Object|/content-docs/api2/reference/GObject/Object#object-set> for all the properties to change, or using L<.configure()|#configure> has the same effect.

=begin code
